===Etymology===
From {{der|en|enm|-}}, from the {{der|en|fro|estandart||gathering place, battle flag}}, from Old {{der|en|frk|*standhard|lit=stand firm, stand hard}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|stand|ard|nocat=1}}. Alternative etymology derives the second element from Old {{der|en|frk||*ord|point, spot, place}} (compare {{cog|ang|ord||point, source, vanguard}}, {{cog|de|Standort||location, place, site, position, base|lit=standing-point}}). More at {{l|en|stand}}, {{l|en|hard}}, {{l|en|ord}}.

===Pronunciation

# Falling within an [[accepted]] [[range]] of size, amount, power, quality, etc.
# {{lb|en|of a tree or shrub}} Growing alone as a free-standing plant; not trained on a post etc.
# '''1863''', {{w|Anthony Trollope}}, ''Rachel Ray'':
#: There are women who cannot grow alone as '''standard''' trees;—for whom the support and warmth of some wall, some paling, some post, is absolutely necessary […].
# Having [[recognize]]d [[excellence]] or [[authority]].
#: '''''standard''' works in history; '''standard''' authors''
# Of a [[usable]] or [[serviceable]] grade or quality.
# {{lb|en|not comparable|of a motor vehicle}} Having a [[manual transmission]].
# As [[normally]] [[supplied]] (not [[optional]]).
# {{lb|en|linguistics}} Conforming to the [[standard variety]].


